    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="484"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d484">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2289: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schuyler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-31T17:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 2—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. In reply to your telegram January 30, 6 p.m., the President states that he has
                    been and is taking every possible precaution and telegraphing orders to
                    departmental commanders to arrest any persons attempting revolutionary
                    activities against Honduras. It seems a band of 40 men armed with machetes has
                    been observed on the <pb facs="0677" n="563" xml:id="pg_563"/> frontier of
                    Gotera and orders have now been given to capture them. The only Honduran leader
                    of importance now in this city will be arrested this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Flores is personal representative of Orellana<note n="6" xml:id="d484fn6"
                        >Provisional President of Guatemala.</note> not of the President of Salvador
                    and is now in this city (see my confidential despatch 103, January 6th, page
                        3,<note n="7" xml:id="d484fn7">Not printed.</note> and my telegram January
                    11, 9 p.m.<note n="8" xml:id="d484fn8">Not found in Department
                    files.</note>).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
